----- Original Message -----

> AAAARRRRRRRGGGGGGHHHHHHH!!!  I broke 2 friggin exhaust
> studs on my 1600 DP engine last night.
> Soooooo, anyone have any special tricks other than the
> ones I mentioned for removing these stupid things???
>

Weld a nut to the end of the stud (right in the center). The heat created
will help break the stud free from the head, and will give you something to
grab and turn easier too.

Eric Allred
